\noindent
Given limited propulsion resources, a servicing spacecraft must select a subset of candidate targets such that total mission cost does not exceed available budget. This selection process is inherently combinatorial and can be modeled as a binary optimization problem.
\newline

\noindent
In our work, we consider a simplified formulation in which the cost of collecting each object is approximated using distance derived from TLE-based orbital state vectors. The goal is to maximize the number of objects collected within a fixed mission budget.

